_Split out from #102 (one issue per bug). Found via an AI-assisted code review with manual verification against commit `5f8ce875`._

`EventDispenser::variation` is default-constructed (`""`) and never set from options, yet it is passed to `loadConstants`/`loadTT` for every run. Digitization routines that key calibration data on the variation receive an empty string instead of `"default"` (or the user's choice).

**Affected files**
- `gemc/eventDispenser/eventDispenser.h:67` (`std::string variation;` — no initializer)
- `gemc/eventDispenser/eventDispenser.cc:25-75` (constructor reads `run_weights`, `run`, `n` — never `variation`)
- `gemc/eventDispenser/eventDispenser.cc:143,150` (passes `variation` to `loadConstants`/`loadTT`)
- `gemc/eventDispenser/eventDispenser_options.cc:17-58` (`defineOptions` — no `variation` option)

**Details**
The member is declared without an initializer:

```cpp
/// Variation string passed to digitization routines when loading constants/translation tables.
std::string variation;
```

The constructor never assigns it:

```cpp
string filename  = gopt->getScalarString("run_weights");
userRunno        = gopt->getScalarInt("run");
neventsToProcess = gopt->getScalarInt("n");
```

but `processEvents` forwards it on every run:

```cpp
if (digiRoutine->loadConstants(runNumber, variation) == false) { ... }
...
if (digiRoutine->loadTT(runNumber, variation) == false) { ... }
```

So `variation` is always `""`. Note the geometry side uses `"default"` as the variation default (`gemc/gsystem/gsystem_options.cc:43,94`), so the digitization and geometry sides disagree.

There is currently **no top-level `variation` option** to read: `"variation"` is only defined as a per-system sub-field of the `gsystem` option group (`gsystem_options.cc:94`), and `eventDispenser::defineOptions()` does not define one. So the fix must both define the option and read it.

**Impact**
Any `loadConstantsImpl`/`loadTTImpl` that selects calibration/translation data by variation gets an empty key, silently loading the wrong (or no) constants. Results differ from the geometry, which uses `"default"`. Run-dependent digitization is effectively un-versioned.

**Proposed fix**
Add a top-level `variation` option mirroring the geometry default, then read it in the constructor.

In `gemc/eventDispenser/eventDispenser_options.cc`, inside `defineOptions()`:

```diff
 	// Option: run number
 	help = "Not to be confused with the geant4 run number - g4runno is set automatically \n \n";
 	help += "Example: -run=12\n";
 	goptions.defineOption(GVariable("run", 1, "sets run number"), help);
+
+	// Option: digitization variation (constants / translation-table version selector).
+	help = "Variation passed to digitization routines when loading constants and translation tables.\n";
+	help += "Example: -variation=default\n";
+	goptions.defineOption(GVariable("variation", "default", "digitization constants/TT variation"), help);
```

In `gemc/eventDispenser/eventDispenser.cc`, in the constructor:

```diff
 	string filename  = gopt->getScalarString("run_weights");
 	userRunno        = gopt->getScalarInt("run");
 	neventsToProcess = gopt->getScalarInt("n");
+	variation        = gopt->getScalarString("variation");
```

`getScalarString` is the established accessor (already used for `run_weights` two lines above), so the option resolves to `"default"` unless the user overrides it, matching the geometry-side default.


