_Split out from #102 (one issue per bug). Found via an AI-assisted code review with manual verification against commit `5f8ce875`._

`getGTouchable` hands back the **persistent** `shared_ptr<GTouchable>` stored in `gTouchableMap`, and `ProcessHits` mutates it (trackId, pid, time-cell index) every step. `Initialize()` clears the per-event `touchableVector` but never resets these mutations, so stale per-step state leaks into later events.

**Affected files**
- `gemc/gsd/gsd.cc:206-213` (`getGTouchable` returns `it->second`, the persistent map object)
- `gemc/gsd/gsd.cc:75-91` (`ProcessHits` mutates the returned touchable: `assignTrackId`, `assignPId`)
- `gemc/gsd/gsd.cc:27-47` (`Initialize` clears `touchableVector` only)
- `gemc/gdynamicDigitization/gdynamicdigitization.cc:133-157` (`processTouchableImpl` mutates `stepTimeAtElectronicsIndex`; clones only on index change)
- `gemc/gsd/gsd.h:195,206-213` (`gTouchableMap`, `getGTouchable`)

**Details**
`getGTouchable` returns the registered touchable directly — the same object registered once at construction:

```cpp
auto it = gTouchableMap.find(vname);
if (it != gTouchableMap.end()) { return it->second; }   // persistent, shared
```

`ProcessHits` then mutates that very object in place:

```cpp
std::vector<std::shared_ptr<GTouchable>> thisStepProcessedTouchables =
    digitization_routine->processTouchable(getGTouchable(thisStep), thisStep);
...
for (auto thisGTouchable : thisStepProcessedTouchables) {
    thisGTouchable->assignTrackId(thisStep->GetTrack()->GetTrackID());
    thisGTouchable->assignPId(thisStep->GetTrack()->GetDefinition()->GetPDGEncoding());
```

`processTouchableImpl` likewise writes `stepTimeAtElectronicsIndex` into the same object (`gtouchable->assignStepTimeAtElectronicsIndex(...)` at line 144) and only clones when the index *changes*. So at the end of an event the map's touchable retains the last event's `trackId`, `pid`, and `stepTimeAtElectronicsIndex`.

`Initialize()` resets the per-event identity cache but not the touchable itself:

```cpp
touchableVector.clear();
GHit::clearTrackVertexCache();
```

Because `stepTimeAtElectronicsIndex` persists, the time-window logic in `processTouchableImpl` (which branches on `getStepTimeAtElectronicsIndex() == GTOUCHABLEUNSETTIMEINDEX`) starts the next event already "set" to the previous event's time cell — so the first step of a new event can be misrouted (no clone when one was due, or vice versa). The lingering `trackId`/`pid` are similarly carried over.

**Impact**
Per-event hit identity and time-cell assignment depend on residual state from the previous event. The first hit(s) of each event after the first can be assigned the wrong time cell or wrong track/PID provenance, producing incorrect or merged hits. Subtle and data-dependent — easy to miss in single-event tests.

**Thread-safety:** confirmed safe to fix locally — `gsd.h` documents instances as thread-local and each worker owns its own `gTouchableMap`, so a per-SD clone introduces no cross-thread sharing.

**Proposed fix (primary): clone before mutating, keep the map object pristine**

Operate on a fresh copy so the persistent registry object is never written. `GTouchable` has a public copy constructor (`gtouchable.h:147`).

```diff
 inline std::shared_ptr<GTouchable> getGTouchable(const G4Step* thisStep) {
 	std::string vname = thisStep->GetPreStepPoint()->GetTouchable()->GetVolume()->GetName();

 	auto it = gTouchableMap.find(vname);
-	if (it != gTouchableMap.end()) { return it->second; }
+	// Return a per-step copy: ProcessHits / processTouchable mutate trackId, pid and the
+	// time-cell index, and the registry entry must stay pristine across events.
+	if (it != gTouchableMap.end()) { return std::make_shared<GTouchable>(*it->second); }
 	// If not found, log an error. The calling code assumes a valid pointer.
 	log->error(ERR_DYNAMICPLUGINNOTFOUND, "GTouchable for volume " + vname + " not found in gTouchableMap");
 }
```

This is correct and idempotent: each step starts from the registry's clean identity (which has `stepTimeAtElectronicsIndex == GTOUCHABLEUNSETTIMEINDEX`), and within an event the SD's own `touchableVector` / hit-collection lookup still groups steps by identity via `operator==` (which compares identity, not the mutated per-step fields).

**Alternative:** reset the per-step discriminators in `Initialize()` each event — for every entry in `gTouchableMap`, re-assign `stepTimeAtElectronicsIndex = GTOUCHABLEUNSETTIMEINDEX` (and clear trackId/pid). Lighter on allocation but easy to forget when new mutable fields are added; the clone approach is more robust.


