_Split out from #102 (one issue per bug). Found via an AI-assisted code review with manual verification against commit `5f8ce875`._

one-line summary
`gstreamersMapPtr` keys the streamer map by the format-derived plugin name, so two outputs of the same format (e.g. two `csv` outputs with different filenames) collide and only one survives.

**Affected files**: `gemc/gstreamer/gstreamer.h:607-629` (`gstreamersMapPtr`), `gemc/gstreamer/gstreamer_options.h:94` (`gstreamerPluginName()`)

**Details**: The map key is `gstreamer_plugin`, which is `"gstreamer_" + format + "_plugin"` — derived from format only, not from the output filename:

```cpp
for (const auto& gstreamer_def : gstreamer::getGStreamerDefinition(gopts)) {
    auto        gstreamer_def_thread = GStreamerDefinition(gstreamer_def, thread_id);
    std::string gstreamer_plugin     = gstreamer_def_thread.gstreamerPluginName(); // "gstreamer_<format>_plugin"

    auto streamer = manager.LoadAndRegisterObjectFromLibrary<GStreamer>(gstreamer_plugin, gopts);
    gstreamers->emplace(gstreamer_plugin, streamer);                 // key = plugin/format name

    gstreamers->at(gstreamer_plugin)->define_gstreamer(gstreamer_def_thread);
}
```

With two same-format definitions, the second `emplace` is a no-op (key already present), but `.at(gstreamer_plugin)->define_gstreamer(...)` then rebinds the *first* streamer instance to the *second* definition. Net result: one streamer object, bound to the last definition; the first output's filename/config is lost.

The map key is only ever used as a human-readable label at the iteration sites — `gRunAction.cc:97`, `:158`, `:283` all do `for (const auto &[name, gstreamer]: *map)` and use `name` only in log/error text, calling methods on `gstreamer`. So the key can be changed to any unique string without breaking consumers.

**Impact**: Any configuration with two or more outputs of the same `format` (different `rootname`/filename) silently produces only one output. Triggered whenever a GCard lists e.g. two `csv` or two `json` gstreamer entries.

**Proposed fix**: Key the map by the unique per-output name (`rootname`) while still loading the plugin library by the format-derived plugin name:

```diff
 	for (const auto& gstreamer_def : gstreamer::getGStreamerDefinition(gopts)) {
 		auto        gstreamer_def_thread = GStreamerDefinition(gstreamer_def, thread_id);
 		std::string gstreamer_plugin     = gstreamer_def_thread.gstreamerPluginName();
+		// Unique per-output key so multiple same-format outputs do not collide.
+		const std::string& output_key   = gstreamer_def_thread.rootname;

 		// Load the plugin object for this configured output.
 		auto streamer = manager.LoadAndRegisterObjectFromLibrary<GStreamer>(gstreamer_plugin, gopts);
-		gstreamers->emplace(gstreamer_plugin, streamer);
-
-		// Bind the thread-specialized definition to the plugin instance.
-		gstreamers->at(gstreamer_plugin)->define_gstreamer(gstreamer_def_thread);
+		auto [it, inserted] = gstreamers->emplace(output_key, streamer);
+		if (!inserted) {
+			log->warning("duplicate gstreamer output name '", output_key,
+			             "' - ignoring later definition");
+			continue;
+		}
+
+		// Bind the thread-specialized definition to this (freshly created) plugin instance.
+		it->second->define_gstreamer(gstreamer_def_thread);
 	}
```

Notes:
- `rootname` is already thread-specialized (`GStreamerDefinition(other, tid)` appends `_t<tid>`), so per-thread maps stay unique across threads too.
- `LoadAndRegisterObjectFromLibrary<GStreamer>(gstreamer_plugin, ...)` must return a *new* instance per call for two same-format streamers to be independent. If that factory caches/registers by plugin name and returns the same shared object, this fix exposes that as the next layer to address (each output needs its own `GStreamer` instance because `define_gstreamer` sets per-output state).
- All current iterators (`gRunAction.cc:97,158,283`) use the key only for logging, so the rename is safe.


