_Split out from #102 (one issue per bug). Found via an AI-assisted code review with manual verification against commit `5f8ce875`._

one-line summary
`GRunAction::publish_run_data` calls `normalize_run_data` inside the streamer loop, so with >=2 run streamers the in-place-mutated run data gets divided by `events_processed` once per streamer.

**Affected files**: `gemc/actions/run/gRunAction.cc:283-293` (loop + call at :290), `gemc/actions/run/gRunAction.cc:297-348` (`normalize_run_data` mutates in place)

**Details**: `normalize_run_data` mutates the shared `run_data_collaction` in place — for each normalized variable it replaces the stored value with `value / norm` via `digitized->includeVariable(...)`:

```cpp
digitized->includeVariable(varName, static_cast<double>(intIt->second) / norm);
...
digitized->includeVariable(varName, dblIt->second / norm);
```

`publish_run_data` invokes it once per streamer, inside the loop:

```cpp
for (const auto &[name, gstreamer]: *gstreamer_run_map) {
    if (gstreamer == nullptr) { ... }

    normalize_run_data(run_data_collaction);   // <-- mutates the SAME collection every iteration

    gstreamer->publishRunData(run_data_collaction);
}
```

Because the mutation is persistent on the shared collection, the first streamer publishes `value/N`, the second publishes `value/N^2`, the third `value/N^3`, etc.

**Impact**: Any run with two or more run-mode streamers configured (e.g. a `root` and a `csv` run output) produces wrong normalized run-level observables in every streamer after the first. With a single run streamer the bug is latent.

**Proposed fix**: Normalize exactly once, before the loop. Since `normalize_run_data` is idempotency-unsafe (it re-divides on every call), it must be hoisted out of the loop:

```diff
-	for (const auto &[name, gstreamer]: *gstreamer_run_map) {
-		if (gstreamer == nullptr) {
-			log->error(ERR_STREAMERMAP_NOT_EXISTING, FUNCTION_NAME,
-			           " null gstreamer instance for run streamer ", name);
-		}
-
-
-		normalize_run_data(run_data_collaction);
-
-		gstreamer->publishRunData(run_data_collaction);
-	}
+	// Normalize once: normalize_run_data() mutates run_data_collaction in place and is
+	// NOT idempotent, so it must run exactly once regardless of streamer count.
+	normalize_run_data(run_data_collaction);
+
+	for (const auto &[name, gstreamer]: *gstreamer_run_map) {
+		if (gstreamer == nullptr) {
+			log->error(ERR_STREAMERMAP_NOT_EXISTING, FUNCTION_NAME,
+			           " null gstreamer instance for run streamer ", name);
+		}
+
+		gstreamer->publishRunData(run_data_collaction);
+	}
```

Note: this keeps `normalize_run_data` itself unchanged (still `const`, still in-place). The hoist relies on `publish_run_data` being called once per run; if that ever changes, the in-place mutation would still be a latent double-normalization hazard and `normalize_run_data` should instead be made idempotent.


